  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd0\u0dba 3 \u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dc0 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9d \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The 3-hour power cut will be extended for two more days",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, said this morning (17) that due to the lack of sufficient fuel and water for power generation, the current 3-hour power cut was extended to two days and allowed to continue until tomorrow and the day after (18 and 19).",
        "Accordingly, Mr. Ratnayake said that the electricity will be cut for 3 hours on those two days and the 20 zones from 'A' to 'W' will be cut for 1 hour and 40 minutes during the day and 20 hours and 20 minutes at night.",
        "2 hours and 30 minutes for the 'CC' category, which also includes Colombo cities, from 6.00 am to 8.30 am, and 3 hours from 5.00 am to 8.00 am for M, N, O, X, Y and Z zones. Mr. Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, further said that it was given."
      ],
